# Cursor Rules ā€” Indigo Design System

## Monorepo Structure
- `packages/tokens` ā†’ @indigo/tokens (CSS variables + Tailwind preset)
- `packages/components` ā†’ @indigo/components (React component library) ā€” ensure package.json `"name"` is `"@indigo/components"`
- `apps/storybook` ā†’ dev environment only, never published

## Stack
- React 18+, TypeScript, strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 with @indigo/tokens preset
- In apps (e.g. Storybook), Tailwind v4 uses `@import "tailwindcss"` in CSS; use the @indigo/tokens preset where token utilities are needed
- shadcn/ui with Base UI primitives
- Storybook 10 with Vite builder

## Component Rules
- All components go in `packages/components/src/components/[ComponentName]/`
- Every component needs 4 files:
  - `ComponentName.tsx` ā€” component implementation
  - `ComponentName.types.ts` ā€” props interface and variant types
  - `ComponentName.stories.tsx` ā€” Storybook stories
  - `index.ts` ā€” re-export
- Use named exports in component files
- Export as default in `index.ts`
- Props interfaces live in `.types.ts` ā€” always import from there, never inline

## Figma Naming Conventions
- Figma component names are PascalCase and map directly to React component names ā€” no transformation
- Figma property names are camelCase and map directly to React prop names ā€” no transformation
- Example: Figma component `ButtonGroup`, property `isDisabled` ā†’ React `<ButtonGroup isDisabled />`
- Example: Figma component `TextInput`, property `hasError` ā†’ React `<TextInput hasError />`
- When reading a Figma node via MCP, use the component name and property names exactly as they appear

## Figma MCP Workflow
- When given a Figma node, read all its variables, properties, and slots via the MCP
- Always resolve Figma Variables to their Tailwind class via the Code Syntax property (see below)
- Map Figma auto-layout direction ā†’ `flex-row` or `flex-col`
- Map Figma auto-layout gap ā†’ `gap-ds2-{size}`
- Map Figma padding (uniform) ā†’ `p-ds2-{size}`
- Map Figma padding (per side) ā†’ `pt-ds2-{size} pr-ds2-{size} pb-ds2-{size} pl-ds2-{size}`
- Map Figma horizontal padding ā†’ `px-ds2-{size}`, vertical ā†’ `py-ds2-{size}`
- Map Figma fill color ā†’ the corresponding `bg-ds2-*` token class from Code Syntax
- Map Figma text color ā†’ the corresponding `text-ds2-*` token class from Code Syntax
- Map Figma stroke color ā†’ the corresponding `border-ds2-*` token class from Code Syntax
- Map Figma corner radius ā†’ the corresponding `rounded-ds2-*` token class from Code Syntax
- Map Figma typography style ā†’ the corresponding `ds2-*` typography class
- Map Figma opacity ā†’ Tailwind `opacity-*` utility
- Map Figma shadow ā†’ Tailwind `shadow-*` utility
- Never guess a token ā€” if a Figma variable doesn't have a clear mapping, flag it

## Figma Variable ā†’ Tailwind Class Resolution
- Figma Variables have a Code Syntax property that contains the exact Tailwind class to use
- When reading a node via MCP, always use the Code Syntax value for the class ā€” never infer or guess
- Example: variable `ds2-background-brand-base` has Code Syntax `bg-ds2-brand-base` ā†’ use `bg-ds2-brand-base`
- The token reference section below is a fallback for cases where no Figma node is provided

## Figma Component Variants ā†’ React Props
- Figma variant properties (e.g. `variant=primary|secondary|ghost`) ā†’ string literal union type
- Figma boolean properties (e.g. `isDisabled`, `isLoading`) ā†’ optional boolean React prop
- Figma instance swap properties (slots) ā†’ ReactNode prop (see Slots section below)
- Figma text properties ā†’ string prop or `children`
- Figma enum properties with 2 opposite values ā†’ boolean prop (e.g. `isFullWidth`)
- All variant combinations from Figma must be representable via props ā€” no variant should be unreachable

## Figma Slots
- A slot is a Figma instance swap property ā€” a placeholder that accepts another component
- Slots map to `ReactNode` props in React
- Name the prop exactly as the Figma slot is named (already camelCase)
- Common slot examples:
  - `leadingIcon?: ReactNode` ā€” icon before label
  - `trailingIcon?: ReactNode` ā€” icon after label
  - `avatar?: ReactNode` ā€” avatar inside a list item or header
  - `badge?: ReactNode` ā€” badge overlaid on a component
  - `prefix?: ReactNode` ā€” prefix inside an input
  - `suffix?: ReactNode` ā€” suffix inside an input
  - `emptyState?: ReactNode` ā€” empty state slot inside a container
- Slots that are optional default to `undefined`
- Only render a slot when the prop is provided:
```tsx
  {leadingIcon && (
    <span className="flex items-center fill-ds2-default">
      {leadingIcon}
    </span>
  )}
```
- Never hardcode icon components inside a slot wrapper ā€” keep slots generic
- If a Figma slot is always visible and never empty, make the prop required

## Styling Rules ā€” CRITICAL
- Use ONLY Tailwind utility classes ā€” no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- ALL colours must use ds2- prefixed token classes (e.g. `bg-ds2-brand-base`, `text-ds2-default`)
- ALL spacing must use ds2- prefixed token classes (e.g. `p-ds2-s`, `gap-ds2-m`)
- ALL border radius must use ds2- prefixed token classes (e.g. `rounded-ds2-m`)
- ALL border width must use ds2- prefixed token classes (e.g. `border-ds2-s`)
- NEVER hardcode hex values, pixel values, rem values, or rgba
- NEVER use arbitrary Tailwind values like `bg-[#1856f5]` or `p-[16px]`
- NEVER use Tailwind's default color palette (e.g. `bg-blue-500`, `text-gray-700`)
- NEVER use Tailwind's default spacing scale (e.g. `p-4`, `gap-2`) for component spacing
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional and merged class logic
- Dark mode via `dark:` variant only ā€” never toggle manually

