## Variants Pattern ā€” use cva
- Import `cva` and `type VariantProps` from `class-variance-authority`
- Define base classes and all variant maps in the component file
- Always use token classes inside cva ā€” never hardcoded values
- Expose VariantProps in the component props interface via intersection type
- Example:
```tsx
  const buttonVariants = cva(
    'inline-flex items-center justify-center ds2-button transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ds2-focused disabled:pointer-events-none',
    {
      variants: {
        variant: {
          primary: 'bg-ds2-brand-base text-ds2-inverted hover:bg-ds2-brand-bold',
          secondary: 'bg-ds2-neutral text-ds2-default hover:bg-ds2-neutral-hover',
          ghost: 'bg-transparent text-ds2-default hover:bg-ds2-neutral',
          danger: 'bg-ds2-danger-bold text-ds2-inverted hover:bg-ds2-danger-bold-hover',
        },
        size: {
          sm: 'h-8 px-ds2-xs rounded-ds2-m',
          md: 'h-10 px-ds2-s rounded-ds2-m',
          lg: 'h-12 px-ds2-s rounded-ds2-l',
        },
      },
      defaultVariants: {
        variant: 'primary',
        size: 'md',
      },
    }
  )
```

## Storybook Rules
- Story title format: `'Indigo/ComponentName'`
- Use `satisfies Meta<typeof Component>` pattern
- Export a `Default` story plus one story per significant variant
- Use `argTypes` to expose all props in the Controls panel
- Import component types from `.types.ts`
- Keep stories thin ā€” no business logic in stories
- Example:
```tsx
  const meta = {
    title: 'Indigo/Button',
    component: Button,
    tags: ['autodocs'],
    argTypes: {
      variant: { control: 'select', options: ['primary', 'secondary', 'ghost', 'danger'] },
      size: { control: 'select', options: ['sm', 'md', 'lg'] },
      isDisabled: { control: 'boolean' },
    },
  } satisfies Meta<typeof Button>
```

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements need appropriate aria attributes
- Use semantic HTML ā€” no div-soup for buttons, inputs, links
- Prefer shadcn/ui Base UI primitives for accessibility guarantees
- All focus states must use: `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ds2-focused focus-visible:outline-none` ā€” ensure the tokens preset defines a ring color (e.g. `ring-ds2-focused`) or use `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:outline-none` with ring color from `var(--ds2-border-focused)` if needed
- Disabled states must use: `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none`
- Loading states must set `aria-busy="true"` and `aria-disabled="true"`

## Do Not
- Do not use `any` ā€” type everything explicitly
- Do not install new packages without flagging it first
- Do not create one-off colour or spacing values ā€” if a token is missing, flag it
- Do not touch `packages/components/src/components/ui/` ā€” shadcn territory
- Do not use `@tailwind base/components/utilities` ā€” Tailwind v4 uses `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Do not add legacy DS1 or non-ds2- classes to any new component
- Do not hardcode font sizes, weights, or line heights ā€” use ds2- typography classes
- Do not use Tailwind's built-in color or spacing scales in components
- Do not transform Figma component or property names ā€” use them exactly as written
